Wells Fargo Chief Says Distressed Homes Should Become Rentals

-- B y   M a r y e l l e n   T i g h e
-- 
2011-10-21T20:45:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-21/wells-fargo-chief-says-distressed-homes-should-become-rentals.html
Wells Fargo & Co. (WFC)  Chief Executive
Officer  John Stumpf  said the housing market could be unclogged
by converting distressed properties into rentals.  Credit is getting better “across the board,” Stumpf,
whose San Francisco-based company is the biggest U.S. home
lender, told Maria Bartiromo on CNBC today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Maryellen Tighe in New York at 
 mtighe6@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
